  "title": "HR cum Office Administrator",
  "description": "<p>Administrative matters:</p><ul><li>Support coordination of company activities or administrative logistics as required</li><li>Maintain confidential HR and administrative records in an organized and secure manner</li><li>Assist leadership with ad-hoc administrative projects and operational support</li><li>Other ad-hoc HR & Administrative duties</li></ul><p>HR Operation:</p><ul><li>Administer day-to-day HR activities including onboarding, probation tracking employee queries, and document preparation</li><li>Track employee performance reviews and probation assessments, assisting line managers with documentation and HR recommendations</li><li>Support and manage recruitment coordination including scheduling, candidate communication, and interview follow-ups</li><li>Manage resignation and exit processes including documentation, employee guidance, and coordination with managers and payroll</li><li>Handle HR matters such as leave handling, insurance, and employee relation queries</li><li>Handle government claims</li><li>Training and Development: Source training courses relevant to staff upgrading and career development</li><li>Ensure compliance with local labor laws and company policies in all HR processes, keeping management informed of updates or potential issues</li><li>Support HR reporting and analytics, providing insights into headcount, leave trends and recruitment progress</li><li>Support cross-border HR processes for overseas staff</li></ul><p>Communication and Documentation:</p><ul><li>Support in policy drafting and dissemination of information</li><li>Draft support letters and documents</li><li>Ensure documents are in proper standard format and follow company’s brand guidelines</li></ul><p>Recruitment:</p><ul><li>Support on JD preparation and ensuring document validity</li><li>Source candidates through job portals</li><li>Screen resumes and shortlist suitable candidates based on role requirements</li><li>HOD conducts first-round HR interviews to assess suitability, cultural fit and salary expectations</li><li>Coordinate end-to-end recruitment logistics including interview scheduling, hiring manager engagement and candidate communication</li><li>Support salary proposal communication and hiring documentation.</li><li>Track candidate pipelines and ensure timely updates to stakeholders.</li></ul><p>**Knowledge of Mandarin would be an advantage to effectively communicate with Mandarin-speaking external stakeholders<br />**Only Singaporeans and SPR are welcome to apply<br />**Salary package will be competitive and commensurate with experience and qualifications</p>",
